Feature: VenueForMoviesVC expanded-list redesign for Home -> Venues -> Map flow (UIKit)

Overview
- Redesign `VenueForMoviesVC` with a polished vertical list style inspired by the expanded trending-list direction.
- Keep current navigation context: HomeVC -> VenuesVC -> MapView -> VenueForMoviesVC.
- Extend each list cell with:
  - movie category
  - screening date
- Data sources are existing endpoints only:
  - category from movies endpoint
  - screening date from screening-date endpoint
- No backend task is included in this feature.

Scope
- In scope: `VenueForMoviesVC` visual redesign, cell hierarchy, UI binding for category/date fields, loading/fallback presentation.
- Out of scope: backend endpoint changes, payload contract changes, authentication/header contract changes.

Functional requirements

REQ-VFM-RD-1 Design baseline
- `VenueForMoviesVC` must follow `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venueformoviesvc-redesign.prototype.html` as the visual review baseline.
- Style direction should align with expanded trending list readability and spacing.

REQ-VFM-RD-2 Vertical list presentation
- Content is displayed as a vertical list (one item per row).
- Rows prioritize clear hierarchy: title, category, screening date, and supporting metadata.

REQ-VFM-RD-3 Category field in cell
- Each row displays movie category.
- Category value is sourced from existing movies endpoint response.
- If category is missing, show neutral fallback text (e.g., `Category: N/A`).

REQ-VFM-RD-4 Screening date field in cell
- Each row displays screening date.
- Screening date value is sourced from existing screening-date endpoint response.
- If date is missing/unavailable, show neutral fallback text (e.g., `Date: TBA`).

REQ-VFM-RD-5 No backend work in this feature
- Do not add new backend endpoints.
- Do not change backend contracts.
- Use existing endpoint payloads and client-side mapping only.

REQ-VFM-RD-6 Flow continuity
- Existing Home -> Venues -> MapView -> VenueForMovies flow remains operational.
- Existing navigation behavior from list item selection remains unchanged.

REQ-VFM-RD-7 UIKit-only constraint
- Implementation remains UIKit-based.
- Do not introduce SwiftUI wrappers or hosting in this scope.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-VFM-RD-NF-1 Performance
- Scrolling remains smooth with new cell metadata fields.
- Additional metadata hydration must not cause visible UI jank.

REQ-VFM-RD-NF-2 Stability
- Existing selection and navigation behavior remains stable.

REQ-VFM-RD-12 Screen background and colors
- Screen background: white (#FFFFFF).
- Navigation buttons (Back, row CTAs): black (#000000), text-filled.
- Row navigation indicators (chevrons › between cells): grayscale light gray (#c2cbe0).
- All text: use NSAttributedString with configurable font family + size.
- Fallback labels (Category: N/A, Date: TBA): medium gray (#808080).

REQ-VFM-RD-13 Icon requirements
- Row navigation chevron: right-pointing › or chevron-right; 15px, light gray (#c2cbe0).
- Movie poster placeholder: film reel icon or placeholder gradient; 52x52px rounded.
- Category metadata icon (optional): 📁 (folder) or generic tag; 12px.
- Screening date icon (optional): 📅 (calendar) or date marker; 12px.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Prototype exists at `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venueformoviesvc-redesign.prototype.html`.
- [ ] Vertical expanded-list style is reflected in prototype hierarchy.
- [ ] Each row includes category and screening date fields.
- [ ] Spec states category source is movies endpoint (existing contract).
- [ ] Spec states screening date source is screening-date endpoint (existing contract).
- [ ] No backend tasks/contracts are introduced.
- [ ] UIKit-only constraint is documented.

Reference files
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venueformoviesvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.homevc-trending-carousel.specify`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenueForMoviesVC.swift`

